<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>B's Batch</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Cookies</cat>
        <cat>And</cat>
        <cat>Bars</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Plus 2 tbsp. sifted all-purpose flour</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Baking soda</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Butter; softened</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Firmly packed brown sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Granulated sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Egg</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Very hot water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Vanilla extract</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Semi-sweet chocolate chips</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.
  
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
  
  2. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
  
  3. Beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and egg in large bowl with electric
  mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes. Beat in hot water and vanilla.
  Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended and smooth. Stir in chocolate
  chips.
  
  4. Drop dough by well-rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto large greased
  baking sheet.
  
  5. Bake in preheated 375 degree oven for 10 minutes or until golden.
  
  6. Cool on sheet on wire rack 1 minute. Remove to wire rack to cool
  completely.
  
